def append_solo(adata, solo_dir):
    d2 = pd.DataFrame()
    for f in set(adata.obs['Sample']):
        if os.path.exists(solo_dir + f + "_mm10_solo_out"):
            solo1 = np.load(solo_dir + f + "_mm10_solo_out/softmax_scores.npy")
            solo2 = np.load(solo_dir + f + "_mm10_solo_out/is_doublet.npy")
            h5ad = sc.read_h5ad(solo_dir + f + "_mm10.h5ad")
            d = pd.DataFrame({'barcode': h5ad.obs.index, 'solo_score': solo1, 'predicted_doublets_solo': solo2})
            d2 = pd.concat([d2,d], axis=0)
        else:
            print("Sample "+ f + " not found")
    d2.index = d2['barcode']
    d2 = d2[['solo_score','predicted_doublets_solo']]
    adata_solo = adata[adata.obs.index.isin(d2.index)]
    tmp=adata_solo.obs
    tmp=tmp.merge(d2, how='inner', left_index = True, right_index = True)
    adata_solo.obs['solo_score'] = tmp['solo_score']
    adata_solo.obs['predicted_doublets_solo'] = tmp['predicted_doublets_solo']   
    return(adata_solo)

def stacked_barplot(adata, xaxis, stack, xaxis_label, legend_label,shift_top=0.2, xaxis_rotation=0):
    tmp=pd.crosstab(adata.obs[xaxis],
                adata.obs[stack]).sum(axis=1)    
    
    ax= pd.crosstab(adata.obs[xaxis],
                    adata.obs[stack]).apply(lambda r: r/r.sum()*100, axis=1)
    ax_1 = ax.plot.bar(figsize=(10,10),stacked=True, rot=0)
    #display(ax)
    #plt.legend(title="Subject") # loc='upper center', bbox_to_anchor=(0.1, 1.0),
    plt.rc('font', size=5)
    plt.legend(loc='best', bbox_to_anchor=(1, 0.5), title=legend_label)
    plt.xlabel(xaxis_label)
    plt.ylabel('Percent Distribution')  
    for rec in ax_1.patches:
        height = rec.get_height()
        ax_1.text(rec.get_x() + rec.get_width() / 2, rec.get_y() + height/2, "{:.0f}%".format(height),
               ha = 'center', va='center') #    
    for xaxistick in range(ax.shape[0]):
        ax_1.text(xaxistick-shift_top,110,tmp[xaxistick],va='center')   
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)    
    ax_1.grid(False)
    plt.show()

def check_and_read(f):
    if os.path.exists(f):
        x=sc.read_10x_h5(f)
        x.obs['Sample']=f.split("/")[-3].split("_")[0]
        x.var_names_make_unique()
        return x
    else:
        print("Sample "+ f + " not found")

Function to calculate the number of nuclei expressing each paralog:

In [146]:
adatac = adata[~adata.obs.Sample.isin(["MM43988","MM43989","MM43990"])]
adatad = adata[adata.obs.Sample.isin(["MM43988","MM43989","MM43990"])]

for n in range(0,len(paralogs)):
    if n % 2 != 0:
        pa = paralogs[n-1]
        pb = paralogs[n]
        for ct in ("CM","FB","EC","MP","PC"):
            rp = adatac[:, [pa, pb]]
            rp = rp[rp.obs.cell_states.isin([ct])]

            ar1 = rp.X[0:rp.shape[0],0].nonzero()[0]
            ar2 = rp.X[0:rp.shape[0],1].nonzero()[0]

            c1 = len(np.intersect1d(ar1,ar2))

            c2 = rp.X[0:rp.shape[0],0].count_nonzero() - c1
            c3 = rp.X[0:rp.shape[0],1].count_nonzero() - c1

            t = rp.shape[0]
            c4 = t-c3-c2-c1
            #print(pa + "/" + pb + "\t" + ct + "\tWT\t" + str(c1) + "\t" + str(c2) + "\t" + str(c3) + "\t" + str(c4))

            rp = adatad[:, [pa, pb]]
            rp = rp[rp.obs.cell_states.isin([ct])]

            ar1 = rp.X[0:rp.shape[0],0].nonzero()[0]
            ar2 = rp.X[0:rp.shape[0],1].nonzero()[0]

            c1 = len(np.intersect1d(ar1,ar2))

            c2 = rp.X[0:rp.shape[0],0].count_nonzero() - c1
            c3 = rp.X[0:rp.shape[0],1].count_nonzero() - c1

            t = rp.shape[0]
            c4 = t-c3-c2-c1
            #print(pa + "/" + pb + "\t" + ct + "\tKO\t" + str(c1) + "\t" + str(c2) + "\t" + str(c3) + "\t" + str(c4))
